body:
I recently found a simulation failing due to the value of a variable with delayed assignment not being initialized to the correct value. While trying to reproduce the problem I found out that I could reproduce with a version recently build from source, but not the version installed in my system (v5.040). I bisect the repo and found out that the bug start happening in commit 94d0513b (which merges #6611).

## Reproduction steps

With this file `delay_dont_update.sv`:

```verilog
`timescale 1ns/1ps

module test;

reg a;
wire b;
initial a = 0;
assign #1 b = a;

always @(a, b) begin
	$display("%d a %b, b %b", $time, a, b);
end

initial begin
	$dumpfile("delay_dont_update.fst");
	$dumpvars(0, test);
	#10 a = 1'b1;
	#10 a = 1'b0;
	#10 $finish;
end

endmodule
```

Run the following command to build and run it:

```
../verilator/bin/verilator delay_dont_update.sv --binary --x-initial unique --debug --runtime-debug --timing --trace-fst &&  obj_dir/Vdelay_dont_update +verilator+rand+reset+1
```

### Observed behavior

On commit 94d0513b the output is:

```
                   0 a 0, b 1
                  10 a 1, b 1
                  20 a 0, b 1
                  21 a 0, b 0
```

Notice that `b` does not became equal to `a` after a delay of `1ns`.

### Expected behavior

A commit prior, 2c01aff2, the output is:

```
                   0 a 0, b 1
                   1 a 0, b 0
                  10 a 1, b 0
                  11 a 1, b 1
                  20 a 0, b 1
                  21 a 0, b 0
```

## Analysis of the problem

Looking at the generated C++ code we see the following code:


```c++
/*delay_dont_update.sv:8 0x55555667c8b0*/VlCoroutine Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0____Vfork_1__0(Vdelay_dont_update___024root* vlSelf);

void Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0(Vdelay_dont_update___024root* vlSelf) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0\n"); );
    Vdelay_dont_update__Syms* const __restrict vlSymsp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSelf->vlSymsp;
    auto& vlSelfRef = std::ref(*vlSelf).get();
    // Body
    if (((IData)(vlSelfRef.test__DOT__a) != (IData)(vlSelfRef.__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0))) {
        Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0____Vfork_1__0(vlSelf);
    }
}

VlCoroutine Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0____Vfork_1__0(Vdelay_dont_update___024root* vlSelf) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0____Vfork_1__0\n"); );
    Vdelay_dont_update__Syms* const __restrict vlSymsp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSelf->vlSymsp;
    auto& vlSelfRef = std::ref(*vlSelf).get();
    // Body
    QData/*63:0*/ __VassignWgen_h726b3455__0__local;
    __VassignWgen_h726b3455__0__local = 0;
    vlSelfRef.__VassignWgen_h726b3455__0 = ((QData)((IData)(1U)) 
                                            + vlSelfRef.__VassignWgen_h726b3455__0);
    __VassignWgen_h726b3455__0__local = vlSelfRef.__VassignWgen_h726b3455__0;
    vlSelfRef.__Vintraval_hccc53e0a__0 = vlSelfRef.test__DOT__a;
    vlSelfRef.__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0 = vlSelfRef.__Vintraval_hccc53e0a__0;
    co_await vlSelfRef.__VdlySched.delay(0x00000000000003e8ULL, 
                                         nullptr, "delay_dont_update.sv", 
                                         8);
    if ((vlSelfRef.__VassignWgen_h726b3455__0 == __VassignWgen_h726b3455__0__local)) {
        vlSelfRef.test__DOT__b = vlSelfRef.__Vintraval_hccc53e0a__0;
    }
}
```

Where `__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0` and `vlSelfRef.test__DOT__b`  are initialized to:

```c++
VL_ATTR_COLD void Vdelay_dont_update___024root___ctor_var_reset(Vdelay_dont_update___024root* vlSelf) {
    VL_DEBUG_IF(VL_DBG_MSGF("+    Vdelay_dont_update___024root___ctor_var_reset\n"); );
    Vdelay_dont_update__Syms* const __restrict vlSymsp VL_ATTR_UNUSED = vlSelf->vlSymsp;
    auto& vlSelfRef = std::ref(*vlSelf).get();
    // Body
    const uint64_t __VscopeHash = VL_MURMUR64_HASH(vlSelf->name());
    /*delay_dont_update.sv:5 0x55555660fb10*/vlSelf->test__DOT__a = VL_SCOPED_RAND_RESET_I(1, __VscopeHash, 258058181390861821ull);
    /*delay_dont_update.sv:6 0x55555660fee0*/vlSelf->test__DOT__b = VL_SCOPED_RAND_RESET_I(1, __VscopeHash, 11931894116788741068ull);
    /// ...
    vlSelf->__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0 = 0;
    /// ...
}
```

So: 
- `__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0` is initially `0` but `test__DOT__b` is `1`, they are out of sync.
- `test__DOT__a` is later set to `0` by the initial block,
- so the code does not enter the `if ((IData)(vlSelfRef.test__DOT__a) != (IData)(vlSelfRef.__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0))`, 
- so `Vdelay_dont_update___024root___act_comb__TOP__0____Vfork_1__0` don't run and `test__DOT__b` is not assignment the value of `__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0`, so they continue out of sync.

On the prior commit both values use the same initialization logic, which works with `+verilator+rand+reset+1`, but I guess it didn't work with randomize initialization, and that is why #6611 exists? I come to this conclusion while writing this paragraph, so I didn't investigate if that is the case.

I believe the proper solution is to somehow always initialize `__VassignWtmp_h3df4871e__0` with  the value of `test__DOT__b`.

## My git bisecting steps

```bash
cd ~/repos/verilator
git bisect start
git bisect bad master
git bisect good v5.040
git bisect run ~/repos/verilator_bug_repro/bisect_test.sh
```

```bash
#!/bin/bash
set -e
cd ~/repos/verilator
NPROC=$(nproc)
make -j$((NPROC-2)) >/dev/null
cd ~/repos/verilator_bug_repro
../verilator/bin/verilator delay_dont_update.sv --binary --x-initial unique --debug --runtime-debug
obj_dir/Vdelay_dont_update +verilator+rand+reset+1 > out.txt

if grep -q "1 a 0, b 0" out.txt; then
  exit 0  # Good
else
  exit 1  # Bad
fi
```
